residents he could never expect them to forget the firebombing of 
dresden in february 1945 
when the war was practically over and this city crowded with 
refugees british and american bombers turned it into a raging 
inferno in which more women and children died than even in 
hiroshima oestreicher said 
but oestreicher also pointed out the horrors of the nazi 
holocaust unleashed by the war that began when hitler invaded poland 
on sept 1 1939 
i cant forget that many of my fathers jewish family were 
killed in german gas chambers said oestreicher who was born in 
germany but fled his homeland in 1939 
an estimated 6 million jews died in the nazi holocaust many of 
them gassed to death in german concentration camps 
on feb 1314 in 1945 combined angloamerican bomber forces 
attacked dresden creating a firestorm that destroyed the heart of 
the city 
incendiary bombs set fire to wooden roofs that were hundreds of 
years old heavy bombs created air suction that whipped up raging 
balls of flames 
estimates of the dead range up to 135000 many of them refugees 
who had fled the russian army that was rapidly advancing on dresden 
93 miles south of berlin 
the skyline of this city of 500000 still shows the marks of war 
