downtown dresden once known for its lovely baroque and 
renaissance facades and spires now has rows of postwar concrete 
structures 
few of the citys old landmarks are still standing 
dresden and its destruction figured prominently in author kurt 
vonnegut jrs acclaimed 1969 novel slaughterhouse five 
