commemorate the cattle drives of the late 1800s the event is the 
biggest planned for montanas 100th birthday 
there have not been this many horsemen together since the 
battle of the little big horn said barry mcwilliams an 
organizer it is stupendous anybody who doesnt see this is 
really going to miss it 
the route of the great montana centennial cattle drive ambles 
south from the musselshell river along us 87 a twolane blacktop 
to stockyards in billings 
organizers faced problems with 20th century environmental 
concerns humane society objections and private property rights 
