economys direction fell to 452 percent last month from 46 percent 
in july that was the lowest reading since december 1982 the month 
after the beginning of the current economic expansion 
bond prices rose on the news as traders believed the slowdown 
could lead the federal reserve to relax credit 
</TEXT>
